results.name: Number of labeled connected bi-point-determining graphs with n vertices (see A129583).
comment: The calculation of connected bi-point-determining graphs is carried out by examining the connected components of bi-point-determining graphs. For more details, see reference.
link: Andrew Howroyd, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..50
Ira M. Gessel and Ji Li, Enumeration of point-determining Graphs, Journal of Combinatorial Theory, Series A 118 (2011) 591-612.
formula: E.g.f.: 1 + x + log((Sum_{n>=0} 2^binomial(n,2)*(2*log(1+x)-x)^n/n!)/(1+x)). - Goran Kilibarda, _Vladeta Jovovic_, May 09 2007
E.g.f.: 1 + x + log(B(x)/(1+x)) where B(x) is the e.g.f. of A129583. - _Andrew Howroyd_, May 06 2021
mathematica: max = 15; f[x_] := x + Log[ Sum[ 2^Binomial[n, 2]*((2*Log[1 + x] - x)^n/n!), {n, 0, max}]/(1 + x)]; A129585 = Drop[ CoefficientList[ Series[ f[x], {x, 0, max}], x]*Range[0, max]!, 1](* _Jean-François Alcover_, Jan 13 2012, after e.g.f. *)
program: (PARI) seq(n)={my(g=sum(k=0, n, 2^binomial(k,2)*x^k/k!) + O(x*x^n)); Vec(serlaplace(1+x+log(subst(g, x, 2*log(1+x+O(x*x^n))-x)/(1+x))))} \\ _Andrew Howroyd_, May 06 2021
